rvice%2Fdigital%2F|title:Digital||" el_class="title line left"][vc_column_text el_class="box"]<p>Lukens Digital is a full-service digital agency</p>\n<p>leveraging digital, data, and technology to help</p>\n<p>organizations reach, engage, and convert their</p>\n<p>target audience online.</p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1499885634825{padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 0px !important;background-image: url(http://lukens/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/marketresearch-h.png?id=227) !important;background-position: center !important;background-repeat: no-repeat !important;background-size: contain !important;}" el_class="right-bg"][vc_column width="1/2" css=".vc_custom_1499890776320{padding-top: 156px !important;padding-right: 115px !important;padding-bottom: 122px !important;}" el_class="text-right"][vc_single_image image="226" img_size="50x50" alignment="right" css=".vc_custom_1499890736755{margin-bottom: 12px !important;}"][vc_custom_heading text="Market research" font_container="tag:h2|font_size:32|text_align:center" use_theme_fonts="yes" link="url:http%3A%2F%2Flukens%2Fservice%2Fmarket-research%2F|title:Market%20research||" el_class="title line right"][vc_column_text el_class="box"]<p>Morey Group is a national market research and</p>\n<p>consulting firm specializing in the unique needs</p>\n<p>of cultural actions.</p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row equal_height="yes" css=".vc_custom_1499884848861{padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 0px !important;background-image: url(http://lukens/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/flbdulge8e8-thomas-kelley-1-.png?id=224) !important;background-position: center !important;background-repeat: no-repeat !important;background-size: contain !important;}" el_class="left-bg"][vc_column width="1/2" el_class="text-right"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2" css=".vc_custom_1499890839503{padding-top: 136px !important;padding-bottom: 109px !important;padding-left: 115px !important;}"][vc_single_image image="201" img_size="60x58" css=".vc_custom_1499890824669{margin-bottom: 10px !important;}"][vc_custom_heading text="Political consulting" font_container="tag:h2|font_size:32|text_align:center" use_theme_fonts="yes" link="url:http%3A%2F%2Flukens%2Fservice%2Fpolitical-consulting%2F|title:Political%20consulting||" el_class="title line left"][vc_column_text el_class="box"]<p>TLC Political specializes in highly creative,</p>\n<p>targeted fundraising and voter contact</p>\n<p>strategies for Republican candidates,</p>\n<p>committees, and causes.</p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_section css=".vc_custom_1499891629119{padding-top: 128px !important;padding-bottom: 105px !important;}" el_class="bg-gradient"][vc_row 0="" el_class="client container"][vc_column el_class="text-center"][vc_custom_heading text="Clients" font_container="tag:h2|text_align:center" use_theme_fonts="yes" el_class="title line" css=".vc_custom_1499891531833{margin-bottom: 12px !important;}"][vc_column_text el_class="box"]<p style="text-align: center;">Inspiring action with great organizations</p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row equal_height="yes" content_placement="middle" css=".vc_custom_1499891392634{padding-top: 30px !important;padding-bottom: 50px !important;}" el_class="client container"][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_single_image image="68" img_size="119x45" alignment="center"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_single_image image="73" img_size="191x57" alignment="center"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_single_image image="229" img_size="171x39" alignment="center"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_single_image image="230" img_size="136x58" alignment="center"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row equal_height="yes" content_placement="middle" css=".vc_custom_1499891411204{padding-top: 40px !important;padding-bottom: 30px !important;}" el_class="client container"][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_single_image image="231" img_size="121x45" alignment="center"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_single_image image="232" img_size="72x70" alignment="center"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_single_image image="233" img_size="75x75" alignment="center"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_single_image image="74" img_size="122x69" alignment="center"][/vc_column][/vc_row][/vc_section][vc_section css=".vc_custom_1499891660669{padding-top: 89px !important;padding-bottom: 124px !important;}"][vc_row el_class="text-center"][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text="CONTACT US" font_container="tag:h3|text_align:center" use_theme_fonts="yes" el_class="section-title line" css=".vc_custom_1499891850042{margin-bottom: -3px !important;}"][vc_column_text el_class="content-wrap" css=".vc_custom_1499891861585{margin-bottom: 33px !important;}"]<p><span style="font-size: 23px;">Let’s continue the conversation.</span></p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="form-wrap"][vc_column][contact-form-7 id="5"][/vc_column][/vc_row][/vc_section]";}s:26:"lukens-case-study-post_100";a:2:{s:4:"name";s:24:"Lukens "Case Study post"";s:8:"template";s:8639:"[vc_section css=".vc_custom_1499937856735{padding-top: 102px !important;padding-bottom: 50px !important;background-color: #ffffff !important;}"][vc_row el_class="container" css=".vc_custom_1499928858235{margin-bottom: 50px !important;}"][vc_column 0=""][vc_column_text el_class="content"]<h2><span style="font-size: 32px;">Background</span></h2>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Founded in 1895, The New York Public Library is the nation’s largest public library system, featuring 88 neighborhood branches throughout the Bronx, Manhattan and Staten Island and four scholarly research centers. The Library is a membership organization offering “soft” benefits such as discounts and invitations to special events. Generating revenue beyond membership dues is a challenge as services are free, the Library receives New York City government funding, and they are in a limited geographic area. In order to grow and diversify the low dollar supporter base, NYPL also mails non-membership special appeals. However, with a monthly renewal cycle, many members were not eligible to receive a special appeal as they were in their renewal cycle and it was not cost effective to mail more than a few packages a fiscal year.</p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="container study-info" css=".vc_custom_1499937724198{margin-bottom: 48px !important;padding-top: 110px !important;}"][vc_column 0=""][vc_row_inner el_class="container-small" css=".vc_custom_1499937473788{margin-bottom: 22px !important;}"][vc_column_inner 0=""][vc_single_image image="74" img_size="170x96" alignment="center"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner el_class="container-small" css=".vc_custom_1499929057349{margin-bottom: -12px !important;}"][vc_column_inner width="1/3"][vc_column_text]<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 28px;"><strong>88</strong></span> <span style="font-size: 14px;">Branches</span></p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/3"][vc_column_text]<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 28px;"><strong>3.5m</strong></span> <span style="font-size: 14px;">Served</span></p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/3"][vc_column_text]<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 28px;"><strong>3.1k</strong> <span style="font-size: 14px;">Staff Members</span></span></p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="container" css=".vc_custom_1499937582458{padding-top: 40px !important;}"][vc_column 0=""][vc_column_text el_class="content"]<h2><span style="font-size: 32px; color: #79a22e;">TLC </br>solution</span></h2>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">In order to incrementally grow the low dollar supporter base, TLC worked with the Library to move from their monthly renewal series to an annual renewal series. The first of the six notice renewal series now mail the end of December and runs through May. This strategy allowed us to free up the third and fourth quarters - the strongest fundraising time of the year - exclusively for special appeals.</p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][/vc_section][vc_section css=".vc_custom_1499937931787{padding-top: 2px !important;padding-bottom: 0px !important;background-color: #f3f3f3 !important;}"][vc_row el_class="container"][vc_column][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1499937909405{margin-bottom: 69px !important;}"]<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 14px; color: #bebebe;"><strong>AUGUST APPEAL</strong></span></p>[/vc_column_text][vc_single_image image="248" img_size="full" alignment="center" css=".vc_custom_1499937974051{margin-bottom: 0px !important;}"][/vc_column][/vc_row][/vc_section][vc_section css=".vc_custom_1499939260440{padding-top: 59px !important;padding-bottom: 30px !important;background-color: #ffffff !important;}"][vc_row el_class="container" css=".vc_custom_1499928858235{margin-bottom: 50px !important;}"][vc_column 0=""][vc_column_text el_class="content"]<p style="text-align: justify;">With the full file eligible for appeals in the fall creating cost efficiencies and savings from running an annual renewal program, TLC was able to increase appeal volumes and add three additional touches in July, September, and April. In FY15, active NYPL donors who renew early would be eligible to receive a total of seven appeals throughout the year.</p>\n<p>The seven different appeal touches also have the added benefit of allowing NYPL to utilize a variety of package formats and highlight many different reasons for supporting the Library; from buying books to promoting education and job placement services. Members and non-member donors alike are able to engage with their Library in whatever way is most meaningful to them.</p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="container study-info" css=".vc_custom_1499938578131{margin-bottom: 36px !important;padding-top: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 80px !important;background-color: #f3f3f3 !important;}"][vc_column 0="" css=".vc_custom_1499938255595{padding-top: 5px !important;}"][vc_row_inner el_class="container-small" css=".vc_custom_1499938405555{margin-bottom: 0px !important;}"][vc_column_inner 0=""][vc_column_text css=".vc_custom_1499938477473{margin-bottom: 40px !important;}"]<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 14px; color: #bebebe;"><strong>AUGUST APPEAL</strong></span></p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner el_class="container-small" css=".vc_custom_1499929057349{margin-bottom: -12px !important;}"][vc_column_inner width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="190" img_size="full" onclick="link_image" el_class="content"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="190" img_size="full" onclick="link_image" el_class="content"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="container" css=".vc_custom_1499932249744{margin-bottom: 40px !important;}"][vc_column 0=""][vc_column_text el_class="content"]<h2><span style="font-size: 32px;">Results</span></h2>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">TLC and NYPL are thrilled with the incremental growth we have seen in the low dollar supporter base. In the four years since implementing this strategy, the number of annual donors has increased 12% and overall gross revenue has increased 7%.</p>\n<p>In addition to the increase in number of donors, response to both the renewal series and appeal series has seen a boost as well. Renewal response rate is up 9% and appeal response rate is up 7% after the four years.</p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row equal_height="yes" content_placement="top" el_class="container" css=".vc_custom_1499938873333{margin-bottom: 16px !important;padding-top: 10px !important;padding-right: 0px !important;padding-bottom: 33px !important;padding-left: 0px !important;}"][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_row_inner el_class="box-shadow" css=".vc_custom_1499938782028{margin-right: 35px !important;padding-top: 43px !important;padding-bottom: 28px !important;}"][vc_column_inner 0=""][vc_column_text]<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><strong>ANNUAL DONORS % GROWTH</strong></span></p>[/vc_column_text][vc_single_image image="249" img_size="full" alignment="center" onclick="link_image"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_row_inner el_class="box-shadow" css=".vc_custom_1499938793189{margin-right: 0px !important;margin-left: 35px !important;padding-top: 43px !important;padding-bottom: 28px !important;}"][vc_column_inner 0=""][vc_column_text]<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><strong>GROSS REVENUE % GROWTH</strong></span></p>[/vc_column_text][vc_single_image image="249" img_size="full" alignment="center" onclick="link_image"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="container" css=".vc_custom_1499932249744{margin-bottom: 40px !important;}"][vc_column 0=""][vc_column_text el_class="content"]<blockquote>\n<p style="text-align: center;">“Working with The Lukens Company has been incredible. The process was totally transparent and the end goals were clearly laid out at the beginning of the process”</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-251 aligncenter" src="http://lukens/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/3db67f8.png" alt="" width="80" height="80" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong>Alexandria Abenshon </strong></span></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 18px;">Librarian</span></p>\n</blockquote>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][/vc_section]";}}', 'no'),
