(14, 1, '2017-07-06 20:40:00', '2017-07-06 20:40:00', '<p>[vc_section css=".vc_custom_1499868342960{padding-bottom: 58px !important;background-color: #ffffff !important;}"][vc_row el_class="container"][vc_column 0="" css=".vc_custom_1500033167119{padding-top: 30px !important;}"][vc_custom_heading text="History" font_container="tag:h2|font_size:68|text_align:left|line_height:1.2" use_theme_fonts="yes" el_class="section-title line left" css=".vc_custom_1499867253391{margin-bottom: 0px !important;}"][vc_column_text el_class="service-sub-title" css=".vc_custom_1499867278515{margin-bottom: 10px !important;}"]</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 32px;"><em>Founded in 1986, The Lukens Company (TLC) is an <strong>award-winning direct response marketing agency.</strong></em></span></p>\r\n<p>[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text el_class="content"]</p>\r\n<p>Our work includes cultural organizations, faith-based missions, and policy driving associations, in addition to Republican political candidates, committees and causes. TLC has offices in Arlington, VA; Glendale, CA; and Charleston, SC.</p>\r\n<p>For cultural, political and national non-profit organizations looking for innovative ways to <strong>raise money, influence minds, and inspire hearts,</strong> The Lukens Company specializes in integrated direct response programs that deliver results. Our <strong>30-year track record of</strong> success serving leading national and local non-profits and political organizations is distinguished by the deep commitment of our staff of professionals to our clients’ missions and the communities in which they live.</p>\r\n<p>Our unique experience in direct response marketing leverages <strong>survey research and data analytics</strong> to create <strong>integrated, multichannel campaigns</strong> that deliver results, time after time. We utilize direct mail, telemarketing, and digital communications to deliver <strong>creative, award-winning programs</strong> that help our clients achieve their goals</p>\r\n<p>[/vc_column_text][vc_single_image image="105" img_size="full" alignment="center" onclick="link_image" css_animation="none" el_class="content"][/vc_column][/vc_row][/vc_section][vc_section css=".vc_custom_1499869582524{padding-bottom: 35px !important;background-color: #f3f3f3 !important;}"][vc_row el_class="container"][vc_column 0=""][vc_custom_heading text="Leadership" font_container="tag:h2|font_size:68|text_align:left|line_height:1.2" use_theme_fonts="yes" el_class="section-title line left"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="container"][vc_column 0=""][vc_custom_heading text="Walter Lukens" font_container="tag:h3|font_size:31|text_align:left" use_theme_fonts="yes" el_class="person-name"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="container" css=".vc_custom_1499869327091{margin-bottom: 50px !important;}"][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_single_image image="178" img_size="full"][/vc_column][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_column_text el_class="content"]</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 18px;">Walter founded The Lukens Company in 1986, and the company has grown and expanded significantly in the years since, due in large part to his passion for arts and cause-related organizations. Originally from the Philadelphia area, Walter grew up attending performances at the Philadelphia Orchestra and Metropolitan Opera with his mother. He continues to be an avid supporter of the </span>arts,<span style="font-size: 18px;"> and is deeply involved in his community. Walter serves on the Board of Directors of Living Classrooms of the National Capital Area and The Campagna Center, organizations that focus their efforts on improving the lives of children.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 18px;">In addition to leading The Lukens Company, Walter is the founder of several other businesses including Pinnacle List Company, Emotive – a metrics-driven online marketing company, and Predictive Data and Analytics. He has been featured in numerous direct response publications, including DM News and Direct Marketing Magazine, as well as The New York Times, The New York Times Sunday Magazine and The Washington Post. Prior to starting TLC, Walter served as a senior advisor to Senator Bob Dole’s 1988 presidential campaign and was active in the Senator’s subsequent national efforts. Walter lives in Alexandria, Virginia.</span></p>\r\n<p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="container"][vc_column 0=""][vc_custom_heading text="Walter Lukens" font_container="tag:h3|font_size:31|text_align:left" use_theme_fonts="yes" el_class="person-name"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="container" css=".vc_custom_1499870764238{margin-bottom: 50px !important;}"][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_single_image image="178" img_size="full"][/vc_column][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_column_text el_class="content"]</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 18px;">Walter founded The Lukens Company in 1986, and the company has grown and expanded significantly in the years since, due in large part to his passion for arts and cause-related organizations. Originally from the Philadelphia area, Walter grew up attending performances at the Philadelphia Orchestra and Metropolitan Opera with his mother. He continues to be an avid supporter of the </span>arts,<span style="font-size: 18px;"> and is deeply involved in his community. Walter serves on the Board of Directors of Living Classrooms of the National Capital Area and The Campagna Center, organizations that focus their efforts on improving the lives of children.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 18px;">In addition to leading The Lukens Company, Walter is the founder of several other businesses including Pinnacle List Company, Emotive – a metrics-driven online marketing company, and Predictive Data and Analytics. He has been featured in numerous direct response publications, including DM News and Direct Marketing Magazine, as well as The New York Times, The New York Times Sunday Magazine and The Washington Post. Prior to starting TLC, Walter served as a senior advisor to Senator Bob Dole’s 1988 presidential campaign and was active in the Senator’s subsequent national efforts. Walter lives in Alexandria, Virginia.</span></p>\r\n<p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="container"][vc_column 0=""][vc_custom_heading text="Walter Lukens" font_container="tag:h3|font_size:31|text_align:left" use_theme_fonts="yes" el_class="person-name"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="container" css=".vc_custom_1499869327091{margin-bottom: 50px !important;}"][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_single_image image="178" img_size="full"][/vc_column][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_column_text el_class="content"]</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 18px;">Walter founded The Lukens Company in 1986, and the company has grown and expanded significantly in the years since, due in large part to his passion for arts and cause-related organizations. Originally from the Philadelphia area, Walter grew up attending performances at the Philadelphia Orchestra and Metropolitan Opera with his mother. He continues to be an avid supporter of the </span>arts,<span style="font-size: 18px;"> and is deeply involved in his community. Walter serves on the Board of Directors of Living Classrooms of the National Capital Area and The Campagna Center, organizations that focus their efforts on improving the lives of children.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 18px;">In addition to leading The Lukens Company, Walter is the founder of several other businesses including Pinnacle List Company, Emotive – a metrics-driven online marketing company, and Predictive Data and Analytics. He has been featured in numerous direct response publications, including DM News and Direct Marketing Magazine, as well as The New York Times, The New York Times Sunday Magazine and The Washington Post. Prior to starting TLC, Walter served as a senior advisor to Senator Bob Dole’s 1988 presidential campaign and was active in the Senator’s subsequent national efforts. Walter lives in Alexandria, Virginia.</span></p>\r\n<p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][/vc_section][vc_section css=".vc_custom_1499871823132{padding-top: 60px !important;padding-bottom: 35px !important;}"][vc_row el_class="container"][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text="Core Values" font_container="tag:h2|font_size:68|text_align:left|line_height:1.2" use_theme_fonts="yes" el_class="section-title line left" css=".vc_custom_1499870508008{margin-bottom: 40px !important;}"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="container"][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="189" img_size="full" onclick="link_image" el_class="content"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_single_image image="190" img_size="full" onclick="link_image" el_class="content"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="container"][vc_column 0=""][vc_custom_heading text="We value people" font_container="tag:h3|font_size:31|text_align:left" use_theme_fonts="yes" el_class="person-name"][vc_column_text el_class="content"]</p>\r\n<p>We believe there is innate value in all people. We act in ways that respect the dignity, uniqueness, and intrinsic worth of every person and celebrate the richness of diversity in human personality, experience, culture, and contribution. We actively seek the best for all people, those who work with us, our clients, partners, their families, and communities, here and across the globe. We practice an open, participative, collaborative, uplifting and empowering style in working relationships. We encourage the professional, personal, and spiritual development of our staff.</p>\r\n<p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="container"][vc_column 0=""][vc_custom_heading text="We change the world for the better" font_container="tag:h3|font_size:31|text_align:left" use_theme_fonts="yes" el_class="person-name"][vc_column_text el_class="content"]</p>\r\n<p>We proudly support and empower mission-serving organizations and individuals who have chosen to devote their life’s work to improve our world. We seek to multiply their work every day by providing unparalleled partnership support and high-quality, exceptional service to our clients’ mission and by encouraging this same attitude of service in our business partners, vendors, and coworkers.</p>\r\n<p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="container"][vc_column 0=""][vc_custom_heading text="We are entrepreneurs" font_container="tag:h3|font_size:31|text_align:left" use_theme_fonts="yes" el_class="person-name"][vc_column_text el_class="content"]</p>\r\n<p>We continuously seek opportunities to evolve, innovate and improve in all aspects of our work, from the strategies and services we offer our clients to the way we approach our jobs. We take risks because we want to be great, not simply good. We are leaders who accept personal responsibility for our commitments, our work, and our relationships. We challenge prevailing assumptions, create new ideas, and discover practical solutions and we are open to change.</p>\r\n<p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="container"][vc_column 0=""][vc_custom_heading text="We have fun and celebrate creativity" font_container="tag:h3|font_size:31|text_align:left" use_theme_fonts="yes" el_class="person-name"][vc_column_text el_class="content"]</p>\r\n<p>It’s no secret . . . we’re a little “out of the box.” And we’re good with that. Having fun and celebrating unique individual and team talents empower creativity and enhance problem-solving, making us better as people and as an agency.</p>\r\n<p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="container"][vc_column 0=""][vc_custom_heading text="We encourage balance and we give back" font_container="tag:h3|font_size:31|text_align:left" use_theme_fonts="yes" el_class="person-name"][vc_column_text el_class="content"]</p>\r\n<p>We are a work hard - play hard group. But while we revel in our work and play to win, we also strongly encourage a perspective that values balance, particularly between work and family. This same perspective motivates a company-wide desire to help those less fortunate, to give back.</p>\r\n<p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][/vc_section][vc_section css=".vc_custom_1499872598868{padding-top: 35px !important;padding-bottom: 40px !important;background-color: #f3f3f3 !important;}"][vc_row el_class="container" css=".vc_custom_1499874503875{margin-bottom: 26px !important;}"][vc_column 0=""][vc_custom_heading text="Core Values" font_container="tag:h2|font_size:68|text_align:left|line_height:1.2" use_theme_fonts="yes" el_class="section-title line left"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="container"][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_custom_heading text="We’re always looking for great talent." font_container="tag:h3|font_size:31|text_align:left" use_theme_fonts="yes" el_class="careers-sub-title " css=".vc_custom_1499874542162{margin-bottom: 22px !important;}"][vc_column_text el_class="content"]</p>\r\n<p>The Lukens Company is a dynamic, growing organization and we are always looking for qualified individuals to become new members of our team. We invite you to submit your resume by clicking on the link below and will contact you should your experience meet our current needs.</p>\r\n<p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2" css=".vc_custom_1499872758454{padding-left: 100px !important;}"][vc_custom_heading text="Current Positions" font_container="tag:h3|font_size:31|text_align:left|color:%23c47013" use_theme_fonts="yes" el_class="careers-sub-title " css=".vc_custom_1499874555790{margin-bottom: 22px !important;}"][vc_column_text el_class="content"]</p>\r\n<p>Position #1<br />\r\n Position #2<br />\r\n Position #3</p>\r\n<p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][/vc_section]</p>', 'Leadership', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'leadership', '', '', '2017-07-14 06:54:34', '2017-07-14 11:54:34', '', 0, 'http://sham.esy.es/leadership/', 0, 'page', '', 0),
